<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-lAkJKVCEk-N-MoL5UTRTLQ" name=",_ID3moMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" guid="-lAkJKVCEk-N-MoL5UTRTLQ" changeDate="2008-12-12T12:36:48.848+0100">
  <sections xmi:id="_Nzzk8MhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Decide which QoS aspects to calculate and how to measure them " guid="_Nzzk8MhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Define QoS parameters to calculate and metrics which will be used to measure the QoS of the composition. Analyse the influence of each service in each QoS parameter. Depending on the functional slice, some QoS aspects, like security, can be influenced in a different way. Weigh the parameters for each service. That weigh will be used later to calculate affected QoS aspects. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_PXNRYMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Measure each service to be used in the composition " guid="_PXNRYMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Using previously defined metrics, measure the QoS for each service. This implies accessing each service to measure some parameters (like response time). Some aspects can be measured, while others depend on the specification (regarding to behaviour, like security). &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Try to simulate a real usage of the services to obtain results which will be similar to the QoS levels that each service will achieve when executing a composition.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;/FONT>&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Qjp2YMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Analyse the QoS that the composition can offer " guid="_Qjp2YMhBEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Gather all the data and calculate the QoS level of the overall composition having in mind the importance of all the parameters for each functionality. That QoS level should be divided in clear sections to ease future description and discovery of the composition exposed like a service. Check if the composition can fulfil the non-functional requirements defined for the overall composition, and try to solve possible problems. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>If the company has experience in similar projects, try to repeat the same policies. It will be easier to calculate QoS levels if the company proposes a standard way to do it.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Note for companies which develop or provide services: In the case the company develops or provides its own services, try to expose the QoS levels in a homogeneous way to make easier the calculations. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Each&#xD;
service to be used can guarantee a certain QoS level. But when those services are working together, those QoS levels could&#xD;
be different, due to the different levels or due to the fact that they use different approaches for transactions or&#xD;
security. For that reason, the QoS level has to be calculated for the overall composition.&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
